  "prompt": "How can I apply for internship at Google? Is there age limit?",
  "response": "Applying for an internship at Google is a straightforward process, but it requires preparation and attention to detail. Here\u2019s a step-by-step guide to help you navigate the application process:\n\n### 1. **Check Eligibility**\n   - **Age Limit**: Google does not have a strict age limit for interns, but most internships are aimed at students currently enrolled in a degree program (undergraduate, graduate, or PhD). Some programs may have specific academic or enrollment requirements.\n   - **Educational Background**: You should be pursuing a degree in a field relevant to the internship (e.g., computer science, engineering, business, design, etc.).\n   - **Skills**: Google looks for candidates with strong technical, analytical, or creative skills, depending on the role.\n\n### 2. **Find Internship Opportunities**\n   - Visit the [Google Careers website](https://careers.google.com/)\n   - Use the search bar to look for internships by keyword, location, or job type.\n   - Filter results by \u201cInternship\u201d roles.\n\n### 3. **Prepare Your Application**\n   - **Resume**: Tailor your resume to highlight relevant skills, projects, and experiences. Google values problem-solving, leadership, and collaborative skills.\n   - **Cover Letter (Optional)**: While not always required, a well-written cover letter can help you stand out. Explain why you\u2019re passionate about Google and how your skills align with the role.\n   - **Transcript (Optional)**: Some internships may ask for an unofficial transcript to verify your enrollment and academic performance.\n\n### 4. **Submit Your Application**\n   - Create an account on the Google Careers portal.\n   - Fill out the application form and upload your resume and any additional documents.\n   - Double-check for errors before submitting.\n\n### 5. **Prepare for Interviews**\n   - If selected, you\u2019ll go through a phone or video screening, followed by technical or behavioral interviews.\n   - **Technical Interviews**: Practice coding problems, algorithms, and data structures (for technical roles).\n   - **Behavioral Interviews**: Be ready to discuss your past experiences, teamwork, and problem-solving abilities.\n\n### 6. **Follow Up**\n   - After applying, monitor your email for updates. Google\u2019s recruitment team may reach out for additional information or interview scheduling.\n\n### 7. **Consider Alternative Opportunities**\n   - While Google is highly competitive, there are other ways to gain experience. Look into programs like Google\u2019s [STEP (Student Training in Engineering Program)](https://buildyourfuture.withgoogle.com/programs/step/) for first- and second-year students or other tech companies.\n\n### Tips:\n   - **Network**: Attend career fairs, hackathons, or Google events to connect with recruiters.\n   - **Be Persistent**: If you don\u2019t get selected, keep improving your skills and reapplying in the future.\n\nGood luck with your application!",
  "temperature": 1.0,
